"title": "6655: forgiveness, application of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6655",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God's forgiveness of believers' sins leads them to pray for his forgiveness of others and to be forgiving in their dealings with other people.</p>\n<h2>Prayers for forgiveness on behalf of others</h2>\n<h3>For God's own people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:30-Exod32:32\">EXO 32:30–32:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:4-Neh1:11\">NEH 1:4–1:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:4-Dan9:19\">DAN 9:4–9:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos7:1-Amos7:6\">AMO 7:1–7:6</a></p>\n<h3>For other human beings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:20-Gen18:33\">GEN 18:20–18:33</a></strong></p>\n<h3>For one's persecutors</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:33-Luke23:34\">LUK 23:33–23:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:43-Matt5:44\">MAT 5:43–5:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:59-Acts7:60\">ACT 7:59–7:60</a></p>\n<h2>Prayers for forgiveness for oneself</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:4\">LUK 11:4</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:12\">MAT 6:12</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:1-Neh9:3\">NEH 9:1–9:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:1-Ps51:17\">PSA 51:1–51:17</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of forgiveness given</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:1-Ps32:5\">PSA 32:1–32:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:1-Isa6:7\">ISA 6:1–6:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:3-John8:11\">JHN 8:3–8:11</a></p>\n<h2>The call to exercise forgiveness</h2>\n<h3>As a principle of life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:37\">LUK 6:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:38-Matt5:48\">MAT 5:38–5:48</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:27-Luke6:36\">LUK 6:27–6:36</a></p>\n<h3>Within the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:12-Col3:13\">COL 3:12–3:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor2:5-2Cor2:11\">2CO 2:5–2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:32\">EPH 4:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:8-1Pet3:9\">1PE 3:8–3:9</a></p>\n<h3>Forgiving enemies</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:17\">PRO 24:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:21-Prov25:22\">PRO 25:21–25:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:44\">MAT 5:44</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:20\">ROM 12:20</a></p>\n<h2>Being forgiven is dependent on forgiving others</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:25-Mark11:26\">MRK 11:25–11:26</a></strong> <em>NIV footnote at verse 26.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:12\">MAT 6:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:4\">LUK 11:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:14-Matt6:15\">MAT 6:14–6:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:21-Matt18:35\">MAT 18:21–18:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:37\">LUK 6:37</a></p>\n<h2>Forgiveness is to be without limits</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:3-Luke17:4\">LUK 17:3–17:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:21-Matt18:22\">MAT 18:21–18:22</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of human forgiveness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:59-Acts7:60\">ACT 7:59–7:60</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:15-Gen50:21\">GEN 50:15–50:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam16:5-2Sam16:11\">2SA 16:5–16:11</a></p>",
